# Real-Time Market Intelligence Pipeline — Architecture & Implementation Plan

## Overview

Build an **end-to-end, dockerized, streaming data engineering pipeline** that ingests real-time stock trades and financial news from **Finnhub**, processes them through **Kafka → Spark Structured Streaming**, enriches news with **HuggingFace NLP sentiment analysis**, stores results in **PostgreSQL + TimescaleDB**, orchestrates with **Apache Airflow**, and visualizes business insights via dashboards.

The project is designed **incrementally** — each phase is self-contained, testable, and builds on the previous one.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **8GB RAM constraint** — This fundamentally shapes our architecture. Every tool choice below is optimized for low memory. We avoid Cassandra (~2GB), Zookeeper (~500MB), and heavy Spark configs. The pipeline will still be production-representative, just resource-conscious.

---

## Architecture Diagram

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph "Data Sources"
        F1["Finnhub WebSocket<br/>(Real-time Trades)"]
        F2["Finnhub REST API<br/>(Company News)"]
    end

    subgraph "Message Broker"
        K["Apache Kafka<br/>(KRaft mode, no Zookeeper)"]
        T1["Topic: trades"]
        T2["Topic: news"]
    end

    subgraph "Stream Processing"
        S["Spark Structured Streaming"]
        NLP["HuggingFace FinBERT<br/>(Sentiment Scoring)"]
    end

    subgraph "Storage"
        PG["PostgreSQL + TimescaleDB"]
        DB1["raw_trades (hypertable)"]
        DB2["raw_news"]
        DB3["ohlcv_1m / ohlcv_5m"]
        DB4["sentiment_scores"]
        DB5["trading_signals"]
    end

    subgraph "Orchestration"
        AF["Apache Airflow<br/>(LocalExecutor)"]
    end

    subgraph "Visualization"
        VIZ["Power BI / Grafana"]
    end

    F1 --> T1 --> S
    F2 --> T2 --> NLP --> S
    S --> PG
    AF -->|"monitors & schedules"| S
    AF -->|"data quality checks"| PG
    PG --> VIZ
```

