## Business Value Narrative

> **Pitch to a business manager:**
> *"This system monitors stock markets in real-time. When financial news breaks, our AI reads the article in milliseconds and scores whether it's positive or negative. We correlate that sentiment with actual price movements to generate early trading signals. The dashboard shows you — in real time — which stocks are being talked about, whether the news is bullish or bearish, and whether the price is following the sentiment or diverging (which itself is a signal)."*

Key business KPIs we'll surface:
- **Sentiment-Price Correlation Score** — Does positive news actually move the stock up?
- **Sentiment Divergence Alerts** — Stock dropping despite positive news = potential opportunity or risk
- **News Volume Spikes** — Sudden surge in articles about a company = something is happening
- **Aggregated Sector Sentiment** — Are tech stocks being talked about positively or negatively today?

---

## RAM Budget (8GB total, ~5.5GB for Docker)

| Service | Estimated RAM | Notes |
|---------|-------------|-------|
| Kafka (KRaft) | ~600MB | No Zookeeper saves ~500MB |
| PostgreSQL + TimescaleDB | ~300MB | Lightweight for our data volume |
| Spark Master | ~256MB | Coordinator only |
| Spark Worker | ~1GB | Single worker, constrained heap |
| Airflow (webserver + scheduler) | ~700MB | SQLite backend, LocalExecutor |
| Python producers (2x) | ~200MB | Trades + News producers |
| Python NLP consumer | ~800MB | DistilBERT model in memory |
| **Total** | **~3.9GB** | Leaves room for OS + Docker overhead |

> [!TIP]
> We won't run everything simultaneously until Phase 5+. In early phases, only 2-3 containers run at a time, keeping RAM usage around 1-2GB.

