## Verification Plan

Each phase has its own verification before moving to the next:

### Phase 1 Verification
```bash
# 1. Start Kafka
docker compose up -d kafka

# 2. Start trade producer
docker compose up -d trade-producer

# 3. Verify messages in Kafka
docker compose exec kafka kafka-console-consumer.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --topic trades --from-beginning --max-messages 10

# 4. Check logs for errors
docker compose logs trade-producer --tail 50
```

### Phase 2 Verification
```bash
# 1. Start PostgreSQL
docker compose up -d postgres

# 2. Verify tables exist
docker compose exec postgres psql -U pipeline -d market_data -c "\dt"

# 3. Start db consumer, wait 60s, check data
docker compose up -d db-consumer
sleep 60
docker compose exec postgres psql -U pipeline -d market_data -c "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM raw_trades;"
```

### Phase 3 Verification
```bash
# 1. Start Spark
docker compose up -d spark-master spark-worker

# 2. Check Spark UI at http://localhost:8080
# 3. Verify OHLCV data appearing
docker compose exec postgres psql -U pipeline -d market_data -c "SELECT * FROM ohlcv_1m ORDER BY time DESC LIMIT 5;"
```

### Phase 4 Verification
```bash
# 1. Start NLP service
docker compose up -d sentiment-analyzer

# 2. Check sentiment scores
docker compose exec postgres psql -U pipeline -d market_data -c "SELECT * FROM sentiment_scores ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 5;"

# 3. Verify signal generation
docker compose exec postgres psql -U pipeline -d market_data -c "SELECT * FROM trading_signals LIMIT 5;"
```

### Phase 5 Verification
```bash
# 1. Start Airflow
docker compose up -d airflow-webserver airflow-scheduler

# 2. Open Airflow UI at http://localhost:8081
# 3. Trigger DAGs manually and verify they complete
# 4. Check task logs in Airflow UI for errors
```

### End-to-End Smoke Test
```bash
# Full pipeline startup
docker compose up -d

# Wait 2 minutes for data to flow
sleep 120

# Verify data at each stage
docker compose exec postgres psql -U pipeline -d market_data -c "
  SELECT 'raw_trades' as table_name, COUNT(*) as row_count FROM raw_trades
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 'raw_news', COUNT(*) FROM raw_news
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 'ohlcv_1m', COUNT(*) FROM ohlcv_1m
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 'sentiment_scores', COUNT(*) FROM sentiment_scores;
"
```

> [!CAUTION]
> **Don't run all services at once until Phase 5+.** With 8GB RAM, running Kafka + Spark + Airflow + NLP simultaneously will likely cause Docker OOM kills. During Phases 1-4, only run the services relevant to that phase.
